<div id="main">
  <h1 class="media-header">Tours</h1>
  <h2>Google Earth Note</h2>
  <p>To appreciate the Tours to a greater degree, the reader may use Google Earth. Simply go to the <a href="https://www.google.com/earth/desktop/">Google Earth website</a> to download the application. In the search box in the upper left corner of the Google Earth window, enter the name of the peak and country you want to visit. For example, the third chapter of <i>Clawing for the Stars</i> tells of my first visit to Llullaillaco, Chile. Enter this in the box, press "search," and it takes you to the peak. Once there, the viewer can zoom all the way down, right to "street" level, and see much of what I saw.</p>
  <% media.each do |tour_info|
    #puts tour_info["shortname"]
    #puts tour_info["name"]
    if tour_info["section"] %>
      <div class="tours-category-div">
        <h1><%= tour_info["name"] %></h1>
        <% tour_info["tours"].each do |section_tours| %>
          <p><a href="/<%= book["shortname"] %>/tours/<%= section_tours["path"] %>"><%= section_tours["name"] %></a></p>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    <% else %>
      <p><a href="/<%= book["shortname"] %>/tours/<%= tour_info["path"] %>"><%= tour_info["name"] %></a></p>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
</div>
